-- Estee Lauder Shares Fall as 2010 Earnings Forecast Trails Some Estimates
-- Carol Wolf
-- 2010-04-27T20:38:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/estee-lauder-shares-decline-as-annual-forecast-trails-some-estimates.html

          
          
             Estee Lauder Cos., the maker of
Clinique and Bobbi Brown cosmetics, fell 4.2 percent in New York
trading after forecasting 2010 earnings that trailed some
analystsâ€™ estimates.  
 Estee Lauder, based in New York, dropped $2.92 to $67.06 at
4:15 p.m. in New York Stock Exchange composite trading. The
shares have risen 39 percent this year.  
 Profit this year may total $2.65 to $2.75 a share before
costs associated with restructuring and the effect of early debt
repayments, the company said today in a statement.  
 Analysts projected earnings of $2.74 a share, the average
of 19 estimates compiled by Bloomberg. One analyst anticipated
profit of as much as $2.98 a share.  
